Reference:
  - 'Application Monitoring in Java with New Relic (Free Setup)' by Integrations Ninjas
  - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=swpi7EVsVhc

Notes:
 - This project is an independent Spring Boot application used to demonstrate New Relic monitoring.
 - No New Relic dependency is added to the application.
 - Monitoring is enabled using the New Relic Java Agent.
 - Sample Order CRUD APIs are implemented using in-memory storage (ConcurrentHashMap).
 - Preloaded sample order data is available when the application starts.
 - Simulated latency is added to generate meaningful transaction traces and performance metrics in New Relic.
 - Spring Boot Actuator is optional and is not required for New Relic monitoring.
 - Running the Application with New Relic Agent
   java -javaagent:D:/dev/github/springboot-newrelic/newrelic-java/newrelic/newrelic.jar -jar target/springboot-newrelic-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar


Create New Relic Key:
 - License key (starts with '291'):
   <license_key>

 - User key (starts with 'NRAK'):
   <user_key>

Steps to configure:
 - Download 'New Relic agent' zip file
   URL: https://download.newrelic.com/newrelic/java-agent/newrelic-agent/9.3.0/
   Zip File:  newrelic-java.zip

 - Copy 'newrelic-java.zip' zip file to project root folder and extract

 - Update the below fields in 'newrelic-java/newrelic.yml' file
   license_key: '291e52123a971d65b93e2a190b4a0ec91fe3NRAL'
   app_name: springboot-newrelic

   development:
     <<: *default_settings
     app_name: springboot-newrelic (Development)

   test:
     <<: *default_settings
     app_name: springboot-newrelic (Test)

   production:
     <<: *default_settings

   staging:
     <<: *default_settings
     app_name: springboot-newrelic (Staging)


Commands:
 cd D:\dev\github\springboot-newrelic>
 mvn clean install
 java -javaagent:D:/dev/github/springboot-newrelic/newrelic-java/newrelic/newrelic.jar -jar target/springboot-newrelic-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar
